      <body>
         <div type="edition" xml:lang="pra-Latn" rendition="class:83225 maturity:83211">
	<!-- class:83225 = southern class Brāhmī, maturity:83209 = middle Brāhmī / maturity:83211 = late Brāhmī  -->
<div type="textpart" n="A"><head xml:lang="eng">Seal</head>
  <ab xml:lang="san-Latn"><!--Seal text wrapped in a block-level element, in this case <ab> because it does not qualify as a paragraph §2.2.2.-->
  <lb n="1"/>br̥hatphalāyana-sagotrasya mahārāja-śrī-jayavarmmaṇaḥ
  </ab>
</div>
<div type="textpart" n="B"><head xml:lang="eng">Plates</head>
  <p>
    <pb n="1r"/>
<lb n="1r1=1"/>bamhanānaṁ sava-gutaja-mahā<lb 
n="1r2=2" break="no"/>janānaṁ janānaṁ <num value="8">8</num> kūdūrahāre
<lb n="1r3=3"/>pāṁṭūrasa bamhadeyasa
  </p>

<p>
<lb n="1b1=4"/>s<seg type="component" subtype="vowel"><gap reason="illegible" quantity="1" unit="component"/></seg>v<seg type="component" subtype="vowel"><gap reason="illegible" quantity="1" unit="component"/></seg>pato vijaya-khaṁdhāvārā
<lb n="1b2=5"/>nagarā kūdūrāto
<lb n="1b1=6"/>maheśvara-pāda-parigahito

<lb n="2r1=7"/>br̥hatphalāyana-sagoto
<lb n="2r2=8"/>rājā siri-jayavaṁmo
<lb n="2r3=9"/>Ānapayati kūdūre
<!--Parabrahma Sastry (2008: 41): Jayavarman = probably 292 to 302.-->

<lb n="2v1=10"/>vāpataṁ Aṁṁhe dāni
<lb n="2v2=11"/>Aṁmha-vejayike ―
<lb n="2v3=12"/>Āyu-vadhanike ca ―

<lb n="3r1=13"/>baṁmhanānaṁ gotama-sagota-
<lb n="3r2=14"/>jāyāparasa savagutajasa
<lb n="3r3=15"/><num value="8">8</num> tānvasa savigajasa ―

<lb n="3v1=16"/>Asiyo <num value="3">3</num> goginjasa
<lb n="3v2=17"/>asiyo <num value="3">3</num> koḍina-sagotasa
<lb n="3v3=18"/>bhavaṁnajasa Asiyo be <num value="2">2</num>

<lb n="4r1=19"/>bhāradāyas rudaveṁnhujasa ―
<lb n="4r2=20"/>Aṁsi divaḍhā ― kaṁnhāyanasa
<lb n="4r3=21"/>Īsaradatajasa aAsi diva[ḍā] ―
<!--(21) diva[ḍā] ― Hultzsch (p. 317 n. 1): read divaḍhā.-->

<lb n="4v1=22"/>Opamaṁnavasa rudaghosajasa
<lb n="4v2=23"/>Aṁsi 1 kosika-sagotasa
<lb n="4v3=24"/>khaṁdarudajasa Aṁsikā[ddhā] caṁ
<!--(24) caṁ ― Hultzsch (p. 317 n. 2): read ca.-->

<lb n="5r1=25"/>janānaṁ 8 Amsiyo 20 4
<lb n="5r2=26"/>kātuna kūḍurahāre gāmaṁ
<lb n="5r3=27"/>pāṁṭuraṁ ― baṁmhadeyaṁ da[d]āma
<!--(26) kātuna ― Hultzsch (p. 317 n. 3): read kātūna.
Parabrahma Sastry (2008: 41): Pamtura = Patura, Tenali tk., Guntur dt.-->

<lb n="5v1=28"/>Etaṁsi taṁ gāma ―
<lb n="5v2=29"/>pāṭūra ― baṁmhadeyaṁ
<lb n="5v3=30"/>kātūna Oyapāpehi 

<lb n="6r1=31"/>Etasa casa gāmasa
<lb n="6r2=32"/>pāṁṭurasa baṁmhadeyaṁ
<lb n="6r3=33"/>kātuna parihāre vitarāma

<lb n="6v1=34"/>Apāpesaṁ Anomasaṁ
<lb n="6v2=35"/>Alonakhādakaṁ ―
<lb n="6v3=36"/>Araṭhasaṁvinayikaṁ ―

<lb n="7r1=37"/>svajātapārihārikaṁ ca
<lb n="7r2=38"/>Etehi naṁ parihārehi
<lb n="7r3=39"/>parihārahi Etaṁ casiṁ gāma[ṁ]

<lb n="7v1=40"/>pātūra[ṁ] ba[ṁ]madheya[ṁ kā]tuna Etha
<lb n="7v2=41"/>nibaṁdhāpehi Aviyena Ānataṁ
<lb n="7v3=42"/>sayaṁ chato siri-Aṭha-satā<!--(40) pātūra[ṁ] ― Read pāṁtūraṁ.--><lb 
n="8r1=43" break="no"/>-viyayo dato paṭikā ―
<lb n="8r2=44"/>saṁva 10 he pa 1 diva 1
<lb n="8r3=45"/>mahā-talavarena ―
<!--(45) mahātala- ― Hultzsch: mahātagi-. ― But see br̥hatphalāyana- (2a1=7).-->

<lb n="8v1=46"/>mahā-daṁḍanāyakena
<lb n="8v2=47"/>bhāpahānavaṁmena ―
<lb n="8v3=48"/>kaṭati ―
<!--Parabrahma Sastry (2008: 41): executor = Mahatalavara Mahadandanayaka Bhapahanavarman. “The titles show the ikshavakau [sic] influence in the administration”-->

  </p>
</div>
